records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The State files an Amended Information which amends the charge to possess cocaine with intent to deliver (>5-15G), contrary to Section 961.41(1m)(cm)2 of the Wisconsin Statutes.
GUILTY plea entered to the amended charge.  Convicted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five and one-half (5.5) years.  That is three (3) years initial confinement followed by two and one-half (2.5) years extended supervision, consecutive to the sentence presently being served.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
3) maintain absolute sobriety;
4) maintain fulltime employment and/or schooling;
5) provide DNA sample;
6) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) have no contact with any known drug dealers or users;
8) pay court costs;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.
Defendant has credit of 119 days.
Minutes.
